a. the product’s compatibility
b. the product’s complexity
c. the product’s observability
d. the product’s trialability

7. At what stage of the new-product development process are most new-product ideas rejected?
a. test marketing
b. business analysis
c. idea screening
d. idea generation

8. Mosaic Labs has developed a chemical compound that prevents mildew in even the most humid climates. The
week after the compound was invented, a group of the firm’s employees got together and listed ways the product
might be used. What is this an example of?
a. focusing grouping
b. brainstorming
c. concept testing
d. screening

9. introductory
b. maturity
c. growth
d. saturation

